🧾 1. Basic POS System – What You Need
Think of POS as: sell → record → update stock → create accounting entry
Core Modules
Products
Category
Stock quantity
Customers
Users / Registered customers / Suppliers
For purchase tracking
Inventory / Stock
Stock in (purchase)
Stock out (sales)

Adjustments
Sales (Main POS Screen)
Discount (item / total)
Tax (optional)

Payment method:
Cash
Bank
Credit (receivable)
Purchases
Purchase order
Purchase invoice
Supplier payable
Returns
Sales return
Purchase return
Payments
Receive from customer
Pay to supplier
Reports
Daily sales
Profit report
Stock report
Customer ledger
Supplier ledger

🔁 2. Transactions (VERY IMPORTANT)
Every POS action should create double-entry accounting records.
Example: Sale (Cash)
Debit → Cash
Credit → Sales
Debit → Cost of Goods Sold
Credit → Inventory

📊 3. Chart of Accounts (COA)
This is your accounting structure.
🟢 Assets
Cash
Bank
Accounts Receivable (Customers)
Inventory
Fixed Assets (optional)
🔵 Liabilities
Accounts Payable (Suppliers)
Loans
Expenses Payable
🟡 Equity
Owner Capital
Retained Earnings
🔴 Income
Sales
Sales Return (contra income)
Discount Given
🟣 Expenses
Cost of Goods Sold (COGS)
Rent Expense
Utility Expense
Salary Expense
Misc Expense

🧠 4. Mapping POS → Accounts (CRITICAL)
Action Debit Credit
Cash Sale Cash Sales
Credit Sale Accounts Receivable Sales
Purchase Inventory Accounts Payable
Cash Purchase Inventory Cash
Expense Paid Expense Cash
Customer Payment Cash Accounts Receivable
Supplier Payment Accounts Payable Cash
Sales Return Sales Return Cash / AR
Purchase Return Accounts Payable Inventory

